# {{lb|en|logic}} The [[connective]] "[[exclusive or]]".
#: ''The '''XOR''' of (0,0) is 0; (0,1) is 1; (1,0) is 1; and (1,1) is 0.''
# {{lb|en|electrical engineering}} A [[logic gate]] that implements "exclusive or".
# {{lb|en|programming}} The symbolic representation that implements "exclusive or".
#: '''''XOR''' can be used to add bits without [[carry]]ing.''
====Usage notes====
* Boolean variables and states ({{l|en|AND}}, {{l|en|OR}}, {{l|en|NOT}}, {{l|en|TRUE}}, {{l|en|FALSE}} etc.) are commonly written in all uppercase in order to distinguish them from the ordinary uses of the words.
